2026-05-16 23:45:18 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #8 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_code({"code": "import pandas as pd, numpy as np\n\nrc_path = '/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/exploratory-qa-eval/.sandbox_isolated/task_1604616_1778975059868/kramabench-archeology-hard-1/files/radiocarbon_database_regional.xlsx'\nclim_path = '/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/exploratory-qa-eval/.sandbox_isolated/task_1604616_1778975059868/kramabench-archeology-hard-1/files/climateMeasurements.xlsx'\n\nrc = pd.read_excel(rc_path, sheet_name='Sheet1')\nclim = pd.read_excel(clim_path, sheet_name='Sheet1')\n\n# Malta span based on first/last recorded people: use date column min/max\nmal_mask = rc['Region'].astype(str).str.contains('Malta', case=False, na=False) | rc['Region'].astype(str).str.contains('Malt', case=False, na=False)\nmal = rc[mal_mask].copy()\nstart_year = float(mal['date'].min())\nend_year = float(mal['date'].max())\nprint('start_year', start_year, 'end_year', end_year)\n\n# climate measurements: columns include Age_ky and K. Interpolate linearly between nearest points.\n# Assume years in ky, but radiocarbon dates are likely in years BP? Here around 6000-6400 => likely cal. years? climate Age_ky same scale.\n# We'll use Age_ky column as ky. Convert to years = Age_ky*1000\nclim_years = clim['Age_ky'].astype(float)*1000.0\nclim_k = clim['K'].astype(float)\n\n# sort by year\norder = np.argsort(clim_years.values)\nclim_years = clim_years.values[order]\nclim_k = clim_k.values[order]\n\n# restrict to range endpoints inclusive\n# Compute interpolated K at start_year and end_year? question asks average potassium from first and last time, assume linearly interpolated between samples.\n# Interpreting as average over interval [start_year,end_year] using linear interpolation of K(y) where K(y) changes linearly between measurement points.\n# We'll sample at all integer years? better use piecewise linear integral.\n\n# Build function to integrate piecewise linear between start and end.\n# We'll traverse segments where y in [start,end]\n\ndef interp_integral(y0,y1):\n    if y1<y0: y0,y1=y1,y0\n    # find indices around\n    # iterate over segments between consecutive climate points\n    total=0.0\n    for i in range(len(clim_years)-1):\n        a=clim_years[i]; b=clim_years[i+1]\n        if b<y0 or a>y1: continue\n        left=max(a,y0); right=min(b,y1)\n        if right<=left: continue\n        # linear between (a,Ka) and (b,Kb)\n        Ka=clim_k[i]; Kb=clim_k[i+1]\n        slope=(Kb-Ka)/(b-a)\n        # integral of (Ka+slope*(x-a)) dx from left to right\n        # = Ka*(right-left)+ slope*[(x-a)^2/2]_{left}^{right}\n        total += Ka*(right-left) + slope*(((right-a)**2 - (left-a)**2)/2)\n    return total\n\narea = interp_integral(start_year, end_year)\navg = area/(end_year-start_year)\nprint('avg', avg)\nprint('avg_round', round(avg,4))\n"}) [toolUseId=call_muYO07IOpHz7ZYXNow4YJHnK]
